observations.recommendation:
We reiterated our prior years’ recommendation that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
a) Inventory Committee to complete the inventory count to prove the existence of the Municipality’s properties, prepare and submit to the Auditor the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) in the prescribed form. Prioritize the reconciliation of the results of the inventory count with the property and accounting records. Any discrepancies found should be investigated, and the necessary adjustment should be made where the error was committed;
b) Municipal Accountant to prepare the necessary journal entry for the reclassification of the completed project to the appropriated PPE account and under Construction in Progress account and henceforth, coordinate with the Municipal Engineering Office for status of each project reported under Construction in Progress;
c) concerned Municipal Officials to submit a request for relief from property accountability and all the required documents for the flooded Work/Zoo Animal to the Commission on Audit to facilitate approval thereof so that the cost be dropped from the books of account; and
d) Municipal Accountant to coordinate with the Engineering Office on road network account so that unreconciled amount on the road network account so that proper adjustment can be made and disclosure in the Notes to Financial Statements on the total road network system of the Municipality at year-end can be made.

We reiterated our prior years’ recommendation that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
a) Inventory Committee to conduct a physical inventory of all the Municipality’s PPE and prepare and submit the required report thereon. Any discrepancies between the inventory report and the accounting and property records should be investigated and make the necessary adjustments where the error was committed;
b) GSO to determine the officials/employees to whom the equipment was issued, and issue the corresponding ARE for each property to pinpoint the direct person accountable and responsible thereon;
c) Municipal Accountant to provide the correct depreciation and make the necessary adjustment for each type of properties of the Municipality;
d) Municipal Engineer to expedite the submission of the complete description and cost segregation of road components for the road projects of the Municipality;
e) GSO to maintain Local Road Inventory and Road Map. LRNPC and RLRN in accordance with COA Circular No. 2015-008; and
f) Municipal Accountant to disclose in the Notes to the Financial Statements the total road network system as required in COA Circular No. 2015-008.

